<h2 id="head-55f8ebc805e65b5b71ddafdae390e3be2bcd69af">Description</h2>
<p>
a Wilderness-Enhanced Sight of Middle Earth 
</p>
<p>
THIS MODULE WILL BE DEDICATED TO ALL THOSE WHO LOVE WILDERNESS TRAVELLING AS MUCH AS DUNGEON CRAWLING 
</p>
<p>
aWESoME is the customized version that I'm actually using for playing ToME. I'd like to share it with you in the hoping it becomes the replacement for standard ToME <img src="./wiki/rightsidebar/img/smile.png" alt=":-)" height="15" width="15"> ...at least until the arriving of ToME 3 <img src="./wiki/rightsidebar/img/sad.png" alt=":-(" height="15" width="15"> ;-))) 
</p>
<p>
I don't care about races, classes, skill, spells, powers, monsters, items and gods. All this stuff is currently good enough for my taste. 
</p>
<p>
My concern was about wilderness. It's both the best and the worst point of ToME. I still remember how I enjoyed exploring it when I was a newbie. But eventually the Middle-earth layout became too know, so I started adding new features just to keep me involved in the game. 
</p>
<p>
aWESoME is built upon the editing of wf_info.txt and w_info.txt. I'm a 16x16 tiles die-hard, so I've designed new tiles for my new features. They are separately <a class="external" href=".modules.t-o-m-e.net/modules/package.php?id=10"><img src="./wiki/rightsidebar/img/moin-www.png" alt="[WWW]" height="11" width="11">downloadable</a>. If you are an ASCII user, please let me know if something looks weird. aWESoME is not intended to support 8x8 tiles. 
</p>
<p>
Since I want aWESoME to keep close to standard ToME, any other change is just a matter of nitpicking. You can find the detailed list in awesome/changes.txt 
</p>
